
Overview of noun topper

The noun topper has 6 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. topper -- (a worker who makes or adds the top to something)
2. topper -- (a worker who cuts tops off (of trees or vegetables etc.))
3. best, topper -- (the person who is most outstanding or excellent; someone who tops all others; "he could beat the best of them")
4. topper -- (an exceedingly good witticism that surpasses all that have gone before)
5. topper -- (a woman's short coat)
6. dress hat, high hat, opera hat, silk hat, stovepipe, top hat, topper, beaver -- (a man's hat with a tall crown; usually covered with silk or with beaver fur)
